        "id": 284385,
        "name": "",
        "username": "tdbe1",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/tdbe1/{size}/55943_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-02-12T20:47:45.238Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is not a solution, and a non-progressive argument. I don’t consider it normal for my image gallery app to be full of folders generated by random separate apps. I have 4 secure web browsers, I save from all to Downloads. I expect to be (and usually am) able to do the same with all the 100 chat apps.</p>\n<p>When a user (first) tries to download something, you should ask the user via the builtin file manager where to save. Maybe they want to save to Pictures (no subfolders). Maybe they want to save everything to Downloads. etc.</p>\n<p>(If permission is an issue, then user can choose among the PERMISSIONLESS easily accessible folders (pictures, downloads, DCIM etc), in which of them and in which manner it will save which types of files or all files.)</p>\n<p>The current behavior is, Signal decides for you, in an opinionated way, which files go into which (generated) (sub)folders. No bueno. Gives you work and trash.</p>",
