        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/tdbe1/{size}/55943_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-02-12T20:53:24.525Z",
        "cooked": "<p>You are not reading my message. It should be TRIVIAL to set signal to NOT create a SUBFOLDER inside Downloads or other Media folders. I’ve developed apps up to android 11, and I’ve never ran into issues with doing this. There are many current apps that can just save to Downloads (no subfolder). So you have tons of leeway here.</p>\n<p>Hell most of my secure chat apps save to the root of Pictures and/or Downloads, wtf.</p>\n<p>PS: My Signal already has Media Storage Permission granted. Whereas other secure chat apps can save to Downloads or Pictures without ANY Storage permissions.</p>",
